name: Notepad#
statement: You want to type the string $$$s$$$, consisting of $$$n$$$ lowercase Latin letters, using your favorite text editor Notepad#. Notepad# supports two kinds of operations: append any letter to the end of the string; copy a continuous substring of an already typed string and paste this substring to the end of the string. Can you type string $$$s$$$ in strictly less than $$$n$$$ operations?
inputFormat: The first line contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 10^4$$$) — the number of testcases. The first line of each testcase contains a single integer $$$n$$$ ($$$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$$$) — the length of the string $$$s$$$. The second line contains a string $$$s$$$, consisting of $$$n$$$ lowercase Latin letters. The sum of $$$n$$$ doesn't exceed $$$2 \cdot 10^5$$$ over all testcases.
outputFormat: For each testcase, print " YES " if you can type string $$$s$$$ in strictly less than $$$n$$$ operations. Otherwise, print " NO ".
